						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Śrīrāma temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1221, Vikāri, Nija-Āshāḍha śu. 15, Tuesday, lunar eclipse, corresponding to 1299 A.D., June 13.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of tax <hi rend="italic">(Pullari)</hi> collected from the lands at Pasavuvēmula by Vishnuvardhana-Chakravarti and Rudradēva for the merit of their parents.</p>						

						</summary>
